<!-- WHY THIS FILE EXISTS: Claude reads this at the start of every session.
It's your "working with me" manual for the AI agent. The better this file,
the less time you spend correcting the same mistakes, and the more the agent
behaves like a collaborator who already knows your project.

HOW TO USE THIS TEMPLATE:
1. Replace everything in [brackets] with your actual content.
2. Read each comment — the comment explains WHY the section exists, not just what to put in it.
3. Delete comments once you understand a section. They're scaffolding, not permanent.
4. Commit this file to git so all collaborators (human and AI) share the same context.

The act of filling this out is itself useful: it forces you to articulate conventions
you've been applying implicitly. -->

