## Key Files

<!-- List the files the agent should know about by default. Without this,
the agent reads whatever seems relevant — which may include files you
don't want touched, and may miss files you care most about.

Be specific about purpose, not just name. "main.tex" tells the agent
nothing; "main.tex (paper body, 4-page limit)" tells it what constraints apply.

Example:
- main.tex          — paper body (4-page limit excluding references)
- references.bib    — bibliography (all citations must resolve)
- src/train.py      — main training script
- src/model.py      — model architecture
- results/          — experiment outputs (read-only; never modify)
- CHANGELOG.md      — log of significant changes -->

- [filename] — [what it is and any constraints that apply]
- [filename] — [what it is and any constraints that apply]

