<!-- VARIANT: ML PAPER (NeurIPS/ICML/ICLR submission)

# Causal Representation Learning — NeurIPS 2026

## Project Overview
NeurIPS 2026 submission on identifiable causal representations from observational data.
Experiments complete. Currently writing the results section; camera-ready deadline May 15.

## Key Files
- main.tex          — paper body (9-page limit excluding references and appendix)
- references.bib    — bibliography (all citations must resolve against Semantic Scholar)
- src/train.py      — main training script; hyperparameters in config/default.yaml
- src/model.py      — encoder and decoder architectures
- results/          — experiment outputs (read-only; regenerate with scripts/run_all.sh)
- rebuttal/         — reviewer response drafts

## Build Commands
  Compile: latexmk -pdf main.tex
  Clean:   latexmk -C
  Tests:   pytest tests/ --tb=short -q
  Format:  black src/ && isort src/

## Conventions
- Cross-references: \cref{} via cleveref — NEVER \ref{}
- Tables: booktabs (\toprule, \midrule, \bottomrule) — NEVER \hline
- Figures: PDF vector export, colorblind-safe palette (seaborn "colorblind" or Okabe-Ito)
- Writing: active voice, no hedging, one claim per sentence; cut "basically", "simply", "just"
- Citations: \citep{} for parenthetical, \citet{} for inline author-year

## Verification Requirements
- All citations must resolve: run /citation-verify before submission
- Document compiles without errors or overfull boxes
- Main text ≤ 9 pages (check: pdfinfo main.pdf | grep Pages)
- All numerical claims in text match results/ outputs
- No \ref{} — grep to confirm: grep -r '\\ref{' main.tex should return nothing

## Common Mistakes
- Uses \ref{} instead of \cref{}
- Adds \hline to tables instead of booktabs
- Invents citations when uncertain — write [CITE NEEDED] and flag it
- Puts new content in main text without asking — page limit is strict; ask first
-->

