<!-- VARIANT: CLINICAL / MEDICAL RESEARCH

# [Study Name] — [Phase/Stage]

## Project Overview
[Phase III RCT / observational cohort / systematic review] on [topic].
Data collection [complete/ongoing]. Currently [analysis stage].
Ethics approval: [reference number]. Pre-registration: [DOI or registry ID].

## Key Files
- protocol.md       — study protocol (do not modify; locked at registration)
- analysis/         — R scripts for primary and secondary endpoints
- data/processed/   — de-identified analysis dataset (never modify manually)
- manuscript/       — paper drafts
- IMPORTANT: data/raw/ contains identifiable data — NEVER read or reference

## Build Commands
  Primary analysis: Rscript analysis/primary_endpoint.R
  All analyses:     make all
  Render report:    Rscript -e "rmarkdown::render('report/results.Rmd')"

## Conventions
- Statistics: report with 95% CI, two-sided p-values; p < 0.05 threshold
- Effect sizes: Cohen's d or OR with CI — never report p-value alone
- Tables: follow CONSORT/STROBE reporting guidelines
- Never suggest removing participants from analysis without protocol justification
- Primary endpoint is pre-specified; any deviation must be flagged as exploratory

## Verification Requirements
- All analyses must reproduce from data/processed/ with a single make command
- No identifiable data in any output, figure, or intermediate file
- Statistical claims cross-checked against analysis output logs
- Ethics disclosure in manuscript acknowledgements section

## Common Mistakes
- Proposes new subgroup analyses without flagging them as post-hoc exploratory
- Uses ANOVA when the protocol specifies mixed-effects model
- Forgets to adjust for pre-specified covariates
-->

