<!-- VARIANT: DATA ANALYSIS PROJECT (Python/R)

# [Project Name] — Data Analysis

## Project Overview
Analysis of [dataset description] to answer [core research question].
Language: [Python/R]. Data: [source, N, key variables].
Stage: [EDA / modeling / write-up].

## Key Files
- notebooks/01_eda.ipynb       — exploratory data analysis
- notebooks/02_modeling.ipynb  — model training and evaluation
- src/preprocess.py            — data cleaning pipeline
- data/raw/                    — original data (READ ONLY — never modify)
- data/processed/              — cleaned datasets (generated by src/preprocess.py)
- outputs/figures/             — all generated figures (regenerate; never hand-edit)

## Build Commands
  Install:    uv sync
  Preprocess: python src/preprocess.py
  Figures:    python src/make_figures.py
  Tests:      pytest tests/ --tb=short -q
  Format:     black src/ && isort src/

## Conventions
- Figures: matplotlib with seaborn "colorblind" palette, PDF export at 300 dpi
- Never hardcode paths — use pathlib.Path and config constants
- Never modify data/raw/ — all transformations happen in src/
- Formatter: black (line length 88); always run before committing

## Verification Requirements
- Tests pass: pytest --tb=short -q
- Full pipeline reproducible from raw data: python src/preprocess.py && python src/make_figures.py
- No hardcoded paths in any script
- Figures export without error; check outputs/figures/ for results

## Common Mistakes
- Modifies data/raw/ instead of creating a new step in src/preprocess.py
- Uses relative paths that break when run from a different directory
- Proposes pip install — this project uses uv; always suggest uv add
-->

