# [Project Title] — [Discipline]

## Project Overview
[Book chapter / journal article / dissertation chapter] on [topic].
Discipline: [history / philosophy / linguistics / STS / etc.].
Stage: [archival research / drafting / revision].
Target venue: [journal name, word limit].

## Key Files
- draft.md          — current manuscript draft
- notes/            — research notes and source summaries
- sources/          — PDFs of primary sources (fair use; do not redistribute)
- references.bib    — bibliography

## Build Commands
  Compile to PDF: pandoc draft.md --citeproc -o draft.pdf
  Word count:     wc -w draft.md

## Conventions
- Citation style: [Chicago author-date / MLA / APA / footnote style]
- Do not paraphrase primary sources without quoting the original first
- Distinguish between primary sources (archives, texts) and secondary sources (scholarship)
- Writing: active voice where possible; discipline-appropriate hedging for interpretive claims
- Translations: always provide original language in footnote or bracket

## Verification Requirements
- All cited works must appear in references.bib
- Direct quotes must include page numbers
- Word count within target range: [X–Y words for main text]
- Any interpretive claim beyond the sources must be explicitly flagged as interpretation

## Common Mistakes
- Paraphrases archival sources without quoting them — always show the original text
- Omits page numbers from direct quotes
- Conflates the author's interpretation with what a source actually says
- Suggests adding claims not supported by the provided sources
